description:
Character Notes

Alice Cable: Her last name is shared by Swamp Thing cast members Matthew Cable and Abby Cable (born Arcane and after marrying Swamp Thing years later, Holland), neither of which appear in the story. Otherwise she's an original character and serves as Alec's love interest.

Anton Arcane: Unlike the original comic origin of Swamp Thing, in this issue it is Anton who causes the birth of the Swamp Thing, being the greedy businessman who's henchmen ambush Holland's lab and cause his death and rebirth as the Swamp Thing. Also, Anton later takes the formula himself to become Holland's nemesis. Apart from being Swamp Thing's enemy, bears little resemblance to his comic counterpart and would be more akin to General Sunderland.

Linda Holland: Alec's sister rather then his wife, thus allowing the Alice/Alec romance to begin before his transformation into Swamp Thing.

Swamp Thing: The least changed of the cast, Swamp Thing was quite similar to his comic character and apart from his supporting cast was essentially the same character as that in the comics of the time.
name: Swamp Thing

volume.name: The Saga of Swamp Thing Annual

description: FLASH FACT: The Joker is revealed, and Thomas Wayne will have to figure out whether he can pull the trigger on his lifelong nemesis
name: Part Three

description:
FLASH FACT: As the war between Amazons and Atlanteans rages on the battlefield around her, Traci must find the strength to stop her father before he rips the world asunder. 
 
Traci 13 has teleported all over the world trying to recruit help to stop her father from launching a satellite targeted to kill 118 million people. But upon returning home, she made the shocking discovery that she was not the only person in her family left with magical abilities. As Traci’s father taps into dark magic to prevent his daughter from sabotaging his plan, Traci is left with no choice but to martyr herself in a last attempt to stop him. Has Traci’s dad crossed so far over to the side of evil that he’d let his daughter die to exact his revenge on the world?
name: This is the World We Hope For

description:
FLASH FACT: The death toll rises as Deathstroke's journey nears its end. But when he finds his daughter, he also finds something else – something he could never have anticipated… 
 
When a mysterious metahuman named Jenny Blitz saves The Ravager and its crew from a fleet of enemy ships, Deathstroke takes her aboard. As the crew learns of their captain’s plans of splitting the treasure they’re looking for with Jenny, they decide to break out into mutiny. While Deathstroke and Jenny fight for their lives and control of The Ravager, they’ll also have to figure out how to get Deathstroke’s daughter, Rose, back from the clutches of The Caretaker. But when Jenny reveals more about her origins, Deathstroke realizes that he may have just found himself the perfect pawn to play in the lethal battle against his enemy.
name: The Treasure

volume.name: Flashpoint: Deathstroke and the Curse of the Ravager

description: Contiene Captain America Reborn Prologue y  Captain America Reborn  #1-6

FLASH FACT: The Secret Seven are being slaughtered from within. Shade the Changing Man must figure out who it is in time, or he will have another team's death on his hands. 
 
With their identities revealed to the world, the Secret Seven are more vulnerable than ever before. So vulnerable in fact, that they start slaughtering each other from within. But who is to blame for these casualties? Which team members can be trusted? Could the rumors that someone on the team is working for Aquaman or Wonder Woman be true? It’ll be up to Shade The Changing Man to figure it out and put a stop to the traitor who is responsible before any more innocent blood is shed. Even if it means sacrificing himself.
name: Part Three: The Area of Madness
